 | A-060 | Sanction submission changes `application_status` and `appraisal_status` to `submitted_to_sanction_committee` but leaves `LoanApplication.current_stage = credit_assessment` until source governance names the corresponding one-of-six SOP stage value. | Source data-model and auth workflow tables name the submitted status but do not name a separate `current_stage` value for sanction; inventing `sanction`, `approval`, or another stage would create a new persisted vocabulary. | `docs/source/data-model.md` loan-application status/§13.1; `docs/source/auth-permissions.md` §20.1; `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §24.5 | 006G and Epic 007 | Medium | Yes | 2026-07-10 | Epic 007 should set a stage only if a source-backed canonical value is added; historical status facts must not be rewritten. |
 | A-061 | Explicitly revalidating a non-draft `legacy_unverified` appraisal must never make an old Credit Manager decision approve newly pinned prerequisite facts. A `review_pending` row may remain pending after revalidation because no terminal review exists; a `reviewed` row must return to draft, clear only its latest-review projection, preserve immutable review history, and require maker resubmission plus a fresh independent review. Rejected/submitted terminal rows remain quarantined until a separately governed repair exists. | ADR-0003 requires conservative provenance and fresh frozen facts, while migration 0005 can downgrade every state but the current repair is draft-only. Preserving a reviewed status after changing its evidence would silently transfer authority to facts the reviewer never saw; reopening is the conservative workflow default. The source does not define a legacy-remediation state machine, so the exception is explicit and reviewable. | `docs/adr/ADR-0003-freeze-appraisal-prerequisite-projections.md`; `docs/adr/ADR-0004-append-only-appraisal-review-decisions.md`; `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §3/§24; `docs/source/data-model.md` §14.4/§34; architecture review `2026-07-10_213352_architecture_review` | 006E4-legacy-appraisal-remediation-and-history-backfill | High | Yes | 2026-07-10 | If governance defines another remediation flow, version the explicit action. Never silently relabel unproven facts, erase immutable review history, or let a pre-remediation review satisfy sanction gating. |
 | A-062 | Witness list/create uses `GET/POST /api/v1/loan-applications/{id}/witnesses/` with narrow `members.witness.read/create` permissions. Compliance Team Member and Company Secretary receive both; Credit Manager and Internal Auditor receive read only. A qualifying witness must match a member name, have verified member KYC, and hold at least one active shareholding with positive shares. | Source schema and S09 make witnesses application-scoped; the permission naming convention and stage matrix state the actions/roles, but the permission catalogue and endpoint map omit exact codes/path, and the sources do not define how persisted shareholding status/count qualifies a shareholder. The nested path and conservative active-positive test are standard defaults that prevent caller-forged verification. | `docs/source/data-model.md` §10.5; `docs/source/screen-spec.md` S09; `docs/source/auth-permissions.md` §11, §12.2, §15.4, §26.4, §34; `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §7.2 | 004E-witness-shareholder-validation and future documentation workflow slices | Medium | Yes | 2026-07-10 | If governance adds canonical witness permission codes, endpoint shape, name-matching rules, or shareholder qualification, version the adapter and seed while preserving application scope and persisted verification evidence. |
+| A-063 | Legacy witness evidence is backfilled only when one `applications.witness.created` audit folio resolves to exactly one shareholding owned by the witness member; all other legacy provenance remains nullable. | 004E2 forbids guessing and requires audit/member/shareholding facts, but the source does not define a historical matching algorithm. Exact folio plus member ownership is the narrowest conservative match and does not reinterpret later status/count. | `docs/source/data-model.md` §10.5, §29-§30; `docs/slices/004E2-witness-evidence-snapshot-and-input-hardening.md`; Epic 004 digest | 004E2-witness-evidence-snapshot-and-input-hardening | Medium | Yes | 2026-07-11 | If authoritative legacy import identifiers become available, a later remediation migration may fill only currently-null evidence; never rewrite already-snapshotted witness evidence. |
diff --git a/docs/working/digests/epic-004-member-kyc-master.md b/docs/working/digests/epic-004-member-kyc-master.md
index 79c0dd807acab41a31beb777bbcc8a780173931e..1974e3dbfd53193b78f4d22b3330fad730f59326
--- a/docs/working/digests/epic-004-member-kyc-master.md
+++ b/docs/working/digests/epic-004-member-kyc-master.md
@@ -13,6 +13,18 @@
   conservative legacy backfill, stable-read tests, a thin application-owned query seam, and
   redundant-index cleanup. M02-FR-009/BR-010 is not fully closed until it lands.
 
+## 004E2 Witness Evidence Hardening
+
+- New witness creation snapshots the exact qualifying shareholding UUID and folio; list/create
+  responses use only that verification-time evidence and do not reselect current holdings.
+- Legacy backfill requires one creation-audit folio and exactly one matching shareholding for the
+  witness member. Missing, conflicting, or ambiguous evidence stays nullable rather than guessed.
+- Malformed JSON and non-object bodies return `400 VALIDATION_ERROR` without witness/audit/workflow
+  writes. Witness list query plus serialization composition now lives behind the application
+  service seam.
+- The named application, PAN-hash, and Aadhaar-hash indexes remain exactly once; their redundant
+  automatic FK/`db_index` companions are removed.
+
 Source extracts opened incidentally during 003K queue sharpening. `docs/source/` remains
 authoritative; the 004A run must still read the full Epic 004 file and named source references
 before implementation.
diff --git a/sfpcl_credit/applications/migrations/0012_witness_verification_evidence.py b/sfpcl_credit/applications/migrations/0012_witness_verification_evidence.py
new file mode 100644
index 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000..09e6c274f16130ca91548908b067edaa855a5783
--- /dev/null
+++ b/sfpcl_credit/applications/migrations/0012_witness_verification_evidence.py
@@ -0,0 +1,83 @@
+import django.db.models.deletion
+from django.db import migrations, models
+
+
+def backfill_witness_evidence(apps, schema_editor):
+    Witness = apps.get_model("applications", "Witness")
+    AuditLog = apps.get_model("identity", "AuditLog")
+    Shareholding = apps.get_model("members", "Shareholding")
+
+    for witness in Witness.objects.filter(verification_shareholding__isnull=True).iterator():
+        audits = AuditLog.objects.filter(
+            action="applications.witness.created",
+            entity_type="witness",
+            entity_id=witness.witness_id,
+        ).order_by("created_at", "audit_log_id")
+        folios = {
+            payload.get("folio_number")
+            for payload in audits.values_list("new_value_json", flat=True)
+            if isinstance(payload, dict) and payload.get("folio_number")
+        }
+        if len(folios) != 1:
+            continue
+        folio_number = next(iter(folios))
+        matches = list(
+            Shareholding.objects.filter(
+                member_id=witness.member_id,
+                folio_number=folio_number,
+            ).values_list("shareholding_id", flat=True)[:2]
+        )
+        if len(matches) != 1:
+            continue
+        Witness.objects.filter(pk=witness.pk, verification_shareholding__isnull=True).update(
+            verification_shareholding_id=matches[0],
+            verification_folio_number=folio_number,
+        )
+
+
+class Migration(migrations.Migration):
+    dependencies = [
+        ("applications", "0011_witness"),
+        ("identity", "0003_portal_member_auth"),
+        ("members", "0008_cancelledcheque_bankaccount_and_more"),
+    ]
+
+    operations = [
+        migrations.AddField(
+            model_name="witness",
+            name="verification_folio_number",
+            field=models.CharField(blank=True, max_length=100, null=True),
+        ),
+        migrations.AddField(
+            model_name="witness",
+            name="verification_shareholding",
+            field=models.ForeignKey(
+                blank=True,
+                null=True,
+                on_delete=django.db.models.deletion.PROTECT,
+                related_name="verified_witnesses",
+                to="members.shareholding",
+            ),
+        ),
+        migrations.AlterField(
+            model_name="witness",
+            name="loan_application",
+            field=models.ForeignKey(
+                db_index=False,
+                on_delete=django.db.models.deletion.PROTECT,
+                related_name="witnesses",
+                to="applications.loanapplication",
+            ),
+        ),
+        migrations.AlterField(
+            model_name="witness",
+            name="pan_hash",
+            field=models.CharField(max_length=128),
+        ),
+        migrations.AlterField(
+            model_name="witness",
+            name="aadhaar_hash",
+            field=models.CharField(max_length=128),
+        ),
+        migrations.RunPython(backfill_witness_evidence, migrations.RunPython.noop),
+    ]
