 | A-062 | Witness list/create uses `GET/POST /api/v1/loan-applications/{id}/witnesses/` with narrow `members.witness.read/create` permissions. Compliance Team Member and Company Secretary receive both; Credit Manager and Internal Auditor receive read only. A qualifying witness must match a member name, have verified member KYC, and hold at least one active shareholding with positive shares. | Source schema and S09 make witnesses application-scoped; the permission naming convention and stage matrix state the actions/roles, but the permission catalogue and endpoint map omit exact codes/path, and the sources do not define how persisted shareholding status/count qualifies a shareholder. The nested path and conservative active-positive test are standard defaults that prevent caller-forged verification. | `docs/source/data-model.md` §10.5; `docs/source/screen-spec.md` S09; `docs/source/auth-permissions.md` §11, §12.2, §15.4, §26.4, §34; `docs/source/api-contracts.md` §7.2 | 004E-witness-shareholder-validation and future documentation workflow slices | Medium | Yes | 2026-07-10 | If governance adds canonical witness permission codes, endpoint shape, name-matching rules, or shareholder qualification, version the adapter and seed while preserving application scope and persisted verification evidence. |
+| A-063 | Legacy witness evidence is backfilled only when one `applications.witness.created` audit folio resolves to exactly one shareholding owned by the witness member; all other legacy provenance remains nullable. | 004E2 forbids guessing and requires audit/member/shareholding facts, but the source does not define a historical matching algorithm. Exact folio plus member ownership is the narrowest conservative match and does not reinterpret later status/count. | `docs/source/data-model.md` §10.5, §29-§30; `docs/slices/004E2-witness-evidence-snapshot-and-input-hardening.md`; Epic 004 digest | 004E2-witness-evidence-snapshot-and-input-hardening | Medium | Yes | 2026-07-11 | If authoritative legacy import identifiers become available, a later remediation migration may fill only currently-null evidence; never rewrite already-snapshotted witness evidence. |
